Glad to hear it worked!

For the dynamic page, what you've got right now with that code is the code for a detail page, not the actual listings page.

Give this code a try for your module. Make sure to replace variables and object references appropriately, as I used a object in my test account to test this out. In my case "hs_object_id" is what I selected for page slugs, so make sure you also change that to the property you are using for yours.

```{# Check if page is a LISTING page #}
{% if dynamic_page_crm_object_type_fqn %}

  {# Get CRM object information based off dynamic page object selection #}
  {% set families = crm_objects(dynamic_page_crm_object_type_fqn, "limit=200","family_name, hs_object_id") %}

  {# Loop through the results to create listing entries #}
  {% for family in families.results %}

    {# Item to be displayed for each listing, wrapped in an anchor to make it clickable into a details page #}
    <a href="{{request.path}}/{{family.hs_object_id}}">
      <p>{{family.hs_object_id}}</p>
    </a>

  {% endfor %}

{# Check if page is a DETAIL page #}
{% elif dynamic_page_crm_object %}

  {# Set easier variable for object properties #}
  {% set family = dynamic_page_crm_object %}

  <h1>{{family.family_name}}</h1>
  <p>{{family.hs_object_id}}</p>

{# Page is not a dynamic page #}
{% else %}

  <h1>Not a dynamic listings page or dynamic object page!</h1>

{% endif %}```
